ll,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover, to hide, to screen; to veil"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to shield, to guard, to safeguard; to shelter"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to shield, to guard, to safeguard; to shelter; to marry off (a girl or a young woman) (as in order to protect her from sin)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover up, to hide, to screen; to enveil","examples":[{"text":"فَجَعَلَ ٱبْنُ ٱلزُّبَيْرِ أَعْمِدَةً فَسَتَّرَ عَلَيْهَا ٱلسُّتُور حَتَّى ٱرْتَفَعَ بِنَاؤُهُ","english":"And Ibn Az-Zubayr made pillars and covered them with curtains to further the building’s erection."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to shield, to guard, to safeguard; to shelter"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to shield, to guard, to safeguard; to shelter; to marry off (a girl or a young woman) (as in order to protect her from sin)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a covering or barrier that shelters and protects or restricts","examples":[{"text":"هَتَكَ اللهُ سِتْرَ الرَّجُلِ","english":"Allah exposed the man [and his deeds]. (literally \"Allah tore the man's cover.\")"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a covering or barrier that shelters and protects or restricts; curtain, drape","examples":[{"text":"فَجَعَلَ ٱبْنُ ٱلزُّبَيْرِ أَعْمِدَةً فَسَتَّرَ عَلَيْهَا ٱلسُّتُورَ حَتَّى ٱرْتَفَعَ بِنَاؤُهُ","english":"And Ibn Az-Zubayr made pillars and covered them up with curtains to further the building’s erection."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a covering or barrier that shelters and protects or restricts; shame, scruple; compunction","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سُتْرَة (sutra)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سِتَار (sitār)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سِتْر (sitr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew סֵתֶר (“hiddenness; secrecy”)."},"ipa":null}